    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="prose">
                <head rend="underline">Preface.</head>
                <p> This book is not about heroes. English Poetry <lb/>is not yet fit to speak of
                    them. </p>
                <p> Nor is it <add place="below">about glory, honour,</add> about <subst>
                        <del rend="overstrike">battles, and glory of battles</del>
                        <add place="above">deeds or lands</add>
                    </subst>
                    <del rend="overstrike">or land,</del>
                    <subst>
                        <del rend="overstrike">or</del>
                        <add place="below">or anything about</add>
                    </subst> any might, <unclear reason="scribbled">majesty</unclear>, <choice>
                        <abbr>domin</abbr>
                        <expan>domin<ex>ion</ex></expan>
                    </choice> or power <lb/>
                    <del rend="overstrike">whatever</del> except War. </p>
                <p>
                    <add place="left">Above all </add>
                    <del rend="overstrike">Its </del>
                    <subst>
                        <add place="above">I am </add>
                        <del rend="overstrike">This book</del>
                    </subst> is <add place="above">
                        <del rend="overstrike"><unclear>center</unclear></del>
                    </add> not concerned with Poetry. <lb/>
                    <subst>
                        <add place="left">My </add>
                        <del rend="overstrike">It's </del>
                    </subst>
                    <add place="above">
                        <del rend="overstrike">The </del>
                    </add> subject <del rend="overstrike">of</del> is War, and the pity of <del
                        rend="overstrike">it</del> War. <lb/> The Poetry is in the pity. </p>
                <p>
                    <del rend="overstrike">I have no hesistation in </del>
                    <del rend="overstrike">making public</del>
                    <lb/>
                    <del rend="overstrike">publishing such</del>
                    <lb/>
                    <subst>
                        <del rend="overstrike">My </del>
                        <add place="above" rend="caret">Yet these</add>
                    </subst> elegies are <add place="above">to this <add place="above">
                            <del rend="overstrike">past </del>
                        </add> generation </add>
                    <del rend="overstrike">not further consolation</del>
                    <lb/> in no sense consolatory <lb/>
                    <del rend="overstrike">The</del> to <del rend="overstrike">this <add place="above">
                            <subst>
                                <del rend="overstrike">a</del>
                                <add place="above">this</add>
                            </subst>
                            <del rend="overstrike">bereaved</del>
                        </add> generation</del>. They may be to the <lb/> next. <del rend="overstrike"
                        >If I thought the letter of this</del>
                    <lb/>
                    <del rend="overstrike">book would last, I now might have </del>
                    <lb/>
                    <del rend="overstrike">used proper names.</del>
                    <add place="above">All a poet can do today is <add place="above">
                            <del rend="overstrike">to</del>
                        </add> warn <del rend="overstrike">children</del>
                    </add>
                    <lb/> That is why the true <del rend="overstrike">War</del> Poets must be truthful.
                    <lb/>
                </p>
                <p>[If I thought the letter of this book would last, I <lb/>
                    <del rend="overstrike">wo </del> might have used proper names; but if the spirit of
                    <lb/> it <add place="above">survives</add> - survives Prussia - <subst>
                        <del rend="overstrike">I </del>
                        <add>my ambition</add>
                    </subst> and those names will <lb/>
                    <del rend="overstrike">be</del>
                    <del rend="overstrike">content</del> have achieved <del rend="overstrike"
                        >themselves</del>
                    <lb/>
                    <del>ourselves</del> fresher fields than Flanders, <lb/> for he, not of war,
                    would he <lb/> sing </p>
            </div>
            
            
